<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know, here=E2=80=99s a trade:<=
/p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You are a big commodity trading firm =
and you can borrow money cheaply from a bank, secured by commodity cargoes.=
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Another, smaller trading firm wou=
ld like to borrow money from=C2=A0<em>you</em>, secured by its commodity ca=
rgoes.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It will pay you more than y=
ou pay the bank, so you collect a nice spread.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-b=
ottom: 5px;">Your risk is that, if the borrower doesn=E2=80=99t pay you bac=
k, you still have to pay the bank back: You have the smaller trading firm=
=E2=80=99s credit risk. This risk is, of course, mitigated by the collatera=
l: If the other firm doesn=E2=80=99t pay you back you can seize its commodi=
ty cargoes.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Fine. Now add a wrinkle: You find out that the=
 commodity cargoes are fake. The trading firm=C2=A0<em>says=C2=A0</em>that =
it has shiploads of nickel as collateral, but actually the ships are full o=
f worthless rocks. What do you do?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One answer is: You terminate the loans and sue=
 the borrower for fraud. There are problems with that: The borrower probabl=
y has some financial problems, the collateral is worthless, you are not get=
ting all of your money back, and you=E2=80=99ll still have to pay back the =
bank.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another answer is: You say =E2=80=9Cwell, nobo=
dy=E2=80=99s perfect, just don=E2=80=99t tell anyone=C2=A0<em>else</em>=E2=
=80=9D and keep the trade going. You keep collecting the spread on the loan=
. If nobody else knows about the rocks, the borrower can keep rolling the l=
oans forever, and you can keep rolling them with your bank, and everything =
is, not fine exactly, but stable. Stable-ish. There is not really an endgam=
e. I suppose you can hope that your borrower will find another lender and c=
ut you out of it? Or you=E2=80=99ll earn enough spread to make it worth it?=
 Or you=E2=80=99ll retire before anyone finds out?=C2=A0This doesn=E2=80=99=
t seem like a=C2=A0<em>good=C2=A0</em>plan, but it is an understandable one=
.</p>
