counter =E2=80=9Cpink sheets=E2=80=9D market, where secondary trading in pr=
e-existing shares takes place. Shares cannot be redeemed, while new shares =
can only be created if Grayscale carries out a private placement exercise, =
meaning there is no arbitrage mechanism to bring prices back in line with t=
he underlying holdings.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">To be clear, these Grayscale trusts are=C2=A0<=
em>not=C2=A0</em>ETFs, because you can=E2=80=99t create or redeem them; if =
they were ETFs they probably wouldn=E2=80=99t trade at those crazy premiums=
. (You=E2=80=99d go buy a ton of Filecoins and give them to Grayscale to ge=
t back trust shares, etc.) But Grayscale=E2=80=99s biggest trust is the one=
 tracking Bitcoin; it has traded at a discount for a long time, but that di=
scount has closed significantly now that everyone expects the trust to conv=
ert into an ETF (and thus allow redemptions). That optimism has been good f=
or the price of Bitcoin too, and for the prices of crypto generally, and al=
so apparently for the prices of Grayscale altcoin trusts.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bitcoin is a popular financial asset, =E2=80=
=9Cdigital gold,=E2=80=9D a possible diversifier for retail and institution=
al investors. Filecoin is =E2=80=A6=C2=A0the payment currency for a <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33591682.259407/aHR0cHM6L=
y9kb2NzLmZpbGVjb2luLmlvL2Jhc2ljcy93aGF0LWlzLWZpbGVjb2lu/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cBb6d3777e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;"> peer-to-peer file storage system</a>? Why would yo=
u buy it in a pink-sheet wrapper? The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/33591682.259407/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ3JheXNjYWxlLmNvbS9jcnl=
wdG8tcHJvZHVjdHMvZ3JheXNjYWxlLWZpbGVjb2luLXRydXN0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB=
92431db5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgro=
und-color: #ccc;">Grayscale Filecoin Trust</a> is tiny (half a million doll=
ars under management), but owning Filecoin that way is (1) less useful and =
(2) vastly more expensive than owning it directly.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One possible answer is of course =E2=80=9Ca la=
ck of understanding=E2=80=9D; again, this stuff is very small. I suppose an=
other answer is, like, =E2=80=9Ccrypto projects like Filecoin are good and =
valuable, and their tokens are sort of like stock in those projects, but th=
e=C2=A0<em>stock exchange for trading those stocks=C2=A0</em>will be the re=
gular stock exchange, not decentralized finance.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0Last year it=
 was almost plausible to think that the crypto financial system might consu=
me the regular financial system, that in the future all the stocks will be =
tokenized. Now it=E2=80=99s more plausible to think the reverse, that the r=
egular financial system will consume the crypto one, that in the future all=
 tokens will be stock-ized.</p>
